913 play Allah Karim! in which both the promise and the problems of the Land of Israel as "Orient" marked the end of Hebrew Orientalism as a viable cultural option.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aExoticism in literature. 0aHebrew literature, Moderny20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish-Arab relations in literature. 0aOrientalism in literature. 0aZionism. 4aHistory. 4aLiterary Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172935540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501729355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501729355/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles